Welcoming life into this world is both exciting and fulfilling, yet also terrifying. There’s a saying I heard a lot growing up that when a mother gives birth, one of her feet is already in her grave. I never quite understood what it meant until I experienced giving birth to our boys. I honestly feel very blessed and lucky to have had a smooth birthing experience back in Mt. Holly, New Jersey. It was rather traumatizing and very rough with our youngest, however,  and to this day, that birth remains  one of the scariest situations I’ve ever experienced in my whole life. | #AD 

That’s why I’m so proud to have the opportunity to share all about Nurture NJ, a statewide initiative launched by First Lady Tammy Murphy (@firstladynewjersey) in 2019 on Maternal Health Awareness Day. Their goal is to make the state of New Jersey the safest and most equitable in the country to give birth by providing families with the support and resources they need. Enter Connecting NJ, a network of agencies and partners that connect families to the best health and social resources available. Did you know that through this program things like free at-home doulas can be made available to you? You can even get affordable healthcare coverage for your family through NJ FamilyCare as well as housing assistance if needed. These are such essential resources that many people in our great state don’t realize they have access to, so I hope you’ll help me spread the word! Check out https://nj.gov/connectingnj/ to learn more and don’t forget to share with new and expecting moms. #connectingNJ #NurtureNJ

#AD | Toys = Clutter. At least, that is how I see it despite decluttering regularly and doing rotations. At the end of the day, if you are a parent who has kids, it is inevitable. Kids will be kids. So how do I approach a typical but quite bothersome challenge? With organization and labels!

One thing I have learned throughout my motherhood journey is that there is no such thing as a manual to get things in order. So I maneuver and adapt. For our family, we have utilized many bins. I have taught the boys to clean up after their mess and to put things away when they are done. Obviously, you can already guess how that is coming along. Our oldest, however, is slowly grasping the benefits of tidying up now that he is learning to read. To make things much easier for all of us, I have created Organization Labels using my @Cricut Maker 3! I have used a FREE premade template from Design Space, written and cut the labels using my #cricut machine, and placed them in front of the bins.

This is why I love my Cricut machine and all its products. Easy to use, straightforward, and can craft things to be used all around the home, at work, or even for a side hustle! Do you own a Cricut machine? What do you love the most about it? If not, what are you waiting for? Let me know your thoughts! #cricutmade
